column12: Improvements in Vibrators for Siphon Recorders used in Working Long Submarine Cables.
column13: 7663. Taylor, T. D. April 2. Telegraphs.-The siphon of a siphon-recorder is vibrated mechanically by a rotating hexagonal or angular cam driven at high speed from the paperfeed mechanism. The shaft B, carrying the hexagonal cam A, is mounted in bearings C in the adjustable bracket K, and is rotated by a flexible band Q passing over a pulley E clamped to one of the wheels of the gearing G that drives the paperfeed wheels H. The cam A revolves between the paper J and the siphon I at a speed of about five hundred revolutions per minute. Reference is made to prior arrangements in which the siphon is vibrated by means of sound-discharges, or by a spring set in motion by an indented wheel, or by an electrically-operated thread.

column12: Improvements in and relating to tracers for automatic machine tools
column13: 924,308. Electric copying machines. BLACKBURN AIRCRAFT Ltd. Sept. 18, 1961 [July 27, 1961], No. 27328/61. Class 38 (6). The stylus A of a template-following copying machine is supported for both axial and angular movement by a spherical bearing S; and through a ball and cone coupling, Fig. 2 (not shown), rocks a pivoted lever B. Movement of lever B moves a T-shaped contact plate G through a push-rod E. Plate G is pivoted at H and restrained by a tension spring M which urges the stylus A outwards. Plate G carries 6 contacts which co-operate with contacts on a further spring-loaded plate J carried by a pivot K at right-angles to pivot H. The contacts 1 close initially on outward movement of the stylus, governing movement of the cutter into the workpiece, and the contacts 2 close on angular movement of the stylus causing rocking of the lever B to control the cutter to move both inwards and sideways. Axial inwards displacement of the stylus further displaces the lever B to close the contacts 3 and move the cutter sideways, and still further displacement of lever B on angular movement of the stylus closes contacts 4 to move the cutter both sideways and outwards, with further inwards axial movement of the stylus causing contacts 5 to close and move the cutter outwards. Any further axial movement of the stylus closes contacts 6 to stop further movement of the cutter.

column12: Absorbent article with multi-layer folded absorbent core
column13: Absorbent laminates and multi-layer, folded absorbent cores comprising the absorbent laminates for use in absorbent articles are presented. Specifically, multi-layer, folded absorbent cores are presented that are formed from an absorbent laminate comprising an absorbent layer between two tissue layers, in which the absorbent core includes a central channel running longitudinally along the core and crenellations profiled along the thickness of the core and providing enhanced liquid distribution across the core surface area or profile and improved liquid absorption into the laminate.

column12: Artículo absorbente con núcleo absorbente plegado de capa múltiple
column13: Un núcleo (200, 400, 500, 600) absorbente que comprende un laminado (100) absorbente de capa múltiple plegado longitudinalmente de al menos tres capas, comprendiendo el laminado (100) absorbente una capa (102) de laminado superior; una capa (104) de laminado inferior; y en el que una capa (106) absorbente está situada entre la capa (102) de laminado superior y la capa (104) de laminado inferior, la capa (106) absorbente comprende más del 90 por ciento en peso de polímero superabsorbente, caracterizado porque - un canal se extiende longitudinalmente a lo largo del laminado absorbente plegado; - un primer conjunto de capas de laminado está situado en un lado del canal y un segundo conjunto de capas de laminado está situado en el otro lado del canal; - una pluralidad de pasajes para líquido situada entre las capas de laminado, - algunos de los pasajes de líquido se abren hacia el canal central y algunos otros pasajes de líquido se abren hacia los lados del laminado plegado, y - bien sea los pasajes que se abren hacia el canal o los pasajes que se abren hacia los lados laminados están separados lateralmente uno de otro para formar un perfil en terraza.

column12: BEARING ASSEMBLY FOR A CHARGING APPARATUS
column13: A bearing assembly for a charging apparatus. The bearing assembly comprises a bearing housing and a shaft. The bearing assembly further comprises a compressor-side bearing bushing and a turbine-side bearing bushing which together support the shaft inside a bearing bore of the bearing housing. The compressor-side bearing bushing is configured differently than the turbine-side bearing bushing.

column12: Bearing assembly for a charging apparatus
column13: A bearing assembly for a charging apparatus. The bearing assembly comprises a bearing housing and a shaft. The bearing assembly further comprises a compressor-side bearing bushing and a turbine-side bearing bushing which together support the shaft inside a bearing bore of the bearing housing. The bearing assembly is configured to supply unequal amounts of lubricant to a compressor-side outer lubrication gap of the compressor-side bearing bushing and to a turbine-side outer lubrication gap of the turbine-side bearing bushing. The bearing assembly is further configured to supply unequal amounts of lubricant to a compressor-side inner lubrication gap of the compressor-side bearing bushing and to a turbine-side inner lubrication gap of the turbine-side bearing bushing.

column12: Method for producing polyisobutene
column13: The invention relates to a method for producing polyisobutene by polymerization of isobutene using an inert diluent and a halogenated Lewis acid as the catalyst. Said method is characterized by contacting a liquid mixture of the isobutene and the inert diluent with the catalyst in the gas chamber of a polymerization device.

column12: Method For Producing Polyisobutene
column13: The present invention relates to a process for preparing polyisobutene by polymerizing isobutene using an inert diluent and a halogen-containing Lewis acid as a catalyst, wherein the isobutene in the form of droplets is contacted with the Lewis acid in a polymerization apparatus.

column12: Antenna with compact LRU array
column13: An element support and thermal control arrangement for an active array antenna, preferably modular, using line-replaceable units (LRUs), includes a radiating-side liquid-cooled cold plate lying parallel with a liquid-cooled TR coldplate. Antenna elements are supported and cooled by the radiating cold plate, and a beamformer lies between the radiating and TR coldplates. A plurality of column coldplates are attached to the rear of the TR coldplate and define bays or volumes in which power LRUs can be fitted in thermal communication with the TR coldplate, the column coldplates, or both.
